headline: KeyCorp price target lowered to $16 from $18 at Truist
summary: Truist analyst Brian Foran lowered the firm’s price target on KeyCorp (KEY) to $16 from $18 and keeps a Hold rating on the shares. The firm lowered its 2025 and 2026 EPS forecast by 1% each to $1.45 and $1.75, respectively, citing slightly lower investment banking fees and net interest income due to lower earning assets, partially offset by slightly lower credit losses and more share buybacks from the second half of 2025.
